metadata.name: Mars
metadata.description:
In the distant skies of red,  
A planet beckons to be tread,  
Its rusted surface a mystery,  
But humanity's curiosity makes history.

We send our starships and rovers,  
To learn about the world that hovers,  
In our Solar System, so far away,  
Perhaps a new home some day.

The journey is long and tough,  
But the hope of discovery will be enough,  
To push us past the limits of our minds,  
And the vast expanse of space to find.

We dream of inhabiting its land,  
A new frontier oh so grand,  
Humanity's never-ending quest,  
For exploration and progress.

We'll build our homes and grow our food,  
In this barren, alien neighborhood,  
We'll create a new civilization,  
A beacon of our greatest imagination.

For we are explorers, adventurers at heart,  
And the stars are our canvas, our art,  
So let us journey to Mars and beyond,  
And create a future in the Cosmic Pond.
